===Noun===
'''ఫిబ్రవరి''' (phibravari)

Following are the native Telugu months the approximate date each begins. The Telugu year begins with "Chaitramu" and ends with "Palgunamu":

# Chaithramu begins March 13th
# Vaisaakhamu begins April 14th
# Jyeshtta begins May 15th
# Aashaadhamu begins June 16th
# Sraavanamu begins July 17th
# Bhaadhrapadamu begins August 17th
# Aasveeyujamu begins September 17th
# Kaarthikamu begins October 16th
# Maargaseershamu begins November 16th
# Pushyamu begins December 14th
# Maakhamu begins January 12th
# Phaalgunamu begins February 14th

